{
  "doc_id": "765",
  "text": "In recent years, several studies have suggested the use of BNP as a screening test for asymptomatic LV dysfunction [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and some authors have reported conflicting results regarding the value of BNP and NT-proBNP in cancer patients undergoing chemotherapy [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] . In our study, we evaluated breast cancer patients treated with chemotherapy regimens containing liposomal doxorubicin and epirubicin with a lower degree of cardiotoxic activity than doxorubicin. At present, this treatment is commonly used in breast cancer patients, and our results may have an important clinical impact. To the best of our knowledge, this is the first study evaluating serial determination of cTnI and NT-proBNP in this subset of patients.",
